03/08/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Zastava munitions plant in the central Serbian city of Kragujevac will start producing NATO-grade M-21 rifles for the Serbia-Montenegro Army, according to factory director Marinko Petrovic. 
Speaking Monday (2 August), he said the plant has sealed two contracts with the defence ministry to supply weapons and other equipment worth 47m euros. 
Production will begin in mid-August. 
(B92, FoNet - 02/08/04)
